<div id="banner">
	<h1>rfc822 has no chance to survive. take your mime.</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>I put together <a href="../2002/im2000">Aaron&#8217;s Internet Mail 2000 Proposal</a> earlier today for the im2000 list. It was sort of fun. Someone complained that the message URIs were &#8220;security through obscurity&#8221; so I did some fun calculations:</p><blockquote>A relatively small 20-character string (like EzYlONo9JI3hnffmyLl8) provides for 7e+35 possibilities. Even if everyone in the world sent 1000 email messages every day for 100 years and stored them all on the same server, you&#8217;d still only have a .0000000000000000003 chance of guessing a valid number.</blockquote></p>

<p class="posted">posted August 13, 2002 12:42 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000505" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

